<div class="row">
     <%= render 'sidebar.html.erb'%>
        <div class="col-lg-9 ">
            <div class="panel panel-primary">
                <div class="panel-heading"><h1>How to import data?</h1></div>
                <div class="panel-body" align="center">
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">First of all you will want to have an account created.&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-check")+" Register", new_user_path, class: ' btn lg btn-primary' ,:style => "display:inline" %>
                    </div>                
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">Now you have to create your guild profile.&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-check")+" Create Guild", new_guild_path, class: ' btn lg btn-primary' ,:style => "display:inline" %>
                    </div>                    
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">Press this button on your guild's page.It's one the left in the controls box.&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<a><%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-cloud-upload")+" Uploading data", '' ,class: 'list-group-item',:style => "display:inline" %></a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">Once you are there paste the text from RaidOps addon in Wildstar and click &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-ok")+" Import", '', class: ' btn lg btn-info' ,:style => "display:inline" %>
                    </div>                   
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">You can see how this will look after import by checking out one of other guilds' profiles. &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-ok")+" All guilds", guilds_path, class: ' btn lg btn-success' ,:style => "display:inline" %>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-footer" align="center"><%= link_to content_tag(:p , '' , :class => "glyphicon glyphicon-export")+" Or you can use uploader...", "#", class: ' btn lg btn-warning' ,:style => "display:inline" %></div>
            </div>
            <div class="panel panel-warning">
                <div class="panel-heading"><h1>How to export data?</h1></div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning">
                        Open main <b>settings window</b>.<br><br>

                        <img class="media-object center-block" src="http://i.imgur.com/eweECHq.png" alt="..." style="align:center">
                    </div>                     
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning">
                        Open Export window by pressing <b>Export/Import</b> button , from the bottom of the settings window.<br><br>

                        <img class="media-object center-block" src="http://i.imgur.com/uhLKuAQ.png" alt="..." style="align:center">
                    </div>                       
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning">
                        Once you are there select <b>"Website Export"</b> and then press <b>export</b> button. Now simply copy string from the box with orange border.<br><br>

                        <img class="media-object center-block" src="http://i.imgur.com/3oCae2t.png" alt="..." style="align:center">
                    </div>                       
                    <div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning">
                        Exported data can be imported back to the addon. <b>Paste the string</b> into the text box , press <b>Import Database</b> button and then press <b>export/import</b> button. <br><br>

                        <img class="media-object center-block" src="http://i.imgur.com/XBECC8m.png" alt="..." style="align:center">
                    </div>                
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</div>